  "texts": [
    "This leads to improved overall concrete integrity and greater resistance to environmental degradation.",
    "Patel et al. [98] found that fine glass powders, particularly GP63, enhance pozzolanic reactivity, resulting in a denser microstructure with improved durability and mechanical properties.",
    "SEM and EDX analyses confirm that glass powder refines the pore structure, reducing pore size and connectivity, which is essential for resisting chloride and sulfate attacks.",
    "Baikerikar et al. [99] observed that both WGP and sand enhance the interfacial transition zone (ITZ) and decrease micro-cracks, particularly with higher glass powder content, thereby improving bond strength between aggregate and cement paste.",
    "Figure 14 exhibits an SEM photo depicting the effect of WGP on the concrete microstructure."
  ]
